				<td colspan="2"><span>We all know about PoSky &amp; PoFear (where FM plain doesn't even go off), but I was raiding in HoHo last night and could not clear aggro from mobs a good distance away even after multiple fades. I had to camp to clear aggro which then had the odd side-effect of transferring my aggro to raid members who were nowhere near (and had not been near) the mobs in question; they were not even in the raid at the time I faded (and no songs were sung post-fade).
<br />

<br />
Anyone else seeing any Fading Memories weirdness like this since 'the fix' last patch? Does FM have a 'radius' now? Is it no longer zone-wide aggro wipe?
<br />

<br />
I just love when they make a 'fix' yet refuse to define what the intended result nor the application of the change happen to be.
<br />

<br />
-Savidge 
<br />
-Quellious
